This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment analysis and lexical resources. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is a common task in IR. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Learning) as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for sentiment analysis. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as sentiment analysis is a common task in AI. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper discusses the use of neural networks for sentiment analysis.
